    3. [http://www.draw.io/]Draw.io: all kinds of diagrams

Keep The Notes

   It's alway better to keep track the changes of your notes and git is a
   nice choice. Therefore, [http://github.com/]GitHub is the almost
   perfect place.

   As for LaTeX,
   [http://www.ctan.org/tex-archive/support/latexdiff/]latexdiff is a tool
   for checking the diff.

   Some programs allows you to keep the markdown notes on a server.
     * [http://raneto.com/]Raneto: Raneto is an open source Knowledgebase
       platform that uses static Markdown files to power your
       Knowledgebase. This one has a nice looking.
     * [http://realms.io/]Realms: Git based wiki written in Python
       Inspired by Gollum, Ghost, and Dillinger. Basic authentication and
       registration included.
     * [http://tiddlywiki.com/]Tiddlywiki: A unique non-linear notebook
       for capturing, organizing and sharing complex information.
     * Some other
       [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-resea
       rch#static-generator]static site generators.

   For experimental research, eLabFTW made a online labnote system:
   [https://www.elabftw.net/]eLabFTW.

Presentation Tools

Keep You Computer Awake

   It is important to keep your computer awake during the presentation.
   Instead of changing the power options, the following tools can also do
   the job.
     * [https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/caffeine/id411246225]Caffeine
       (Mac): As simple as a single click.
     * [https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/amphetamine/id937984704?mt=12]Amph
       etamine (Mac): More configurations involved and more intelligent.

Online Load and Edit

     * [https://prezi.com/]Prezi if you can.
     * [http://slides.com/]slides.com: Easy to use with remote controlled
       page presentation.
     * [https://drive.google.com/]Google Drive: no introduction needed
     * [https://sway.com/]Sway: Microsoft
     * [https://github.com/tantaman/Strut]Strut
     * [https://github.com/harish-io/Impressionist]Impressionist
     * [https://github.com/regebro/hovercraft]hovercraft

