Programming

Code Editors

     * [https://atom.io/]Atom(Free,Cross-platform,Plugins): electron based
       editor with numerous plugins and easy modifications. Cross-platform
       with settings and plugins synchronized through the
       [https://atom.io/packages/sync-settings]sync-settings plugin.
     * [https://code.visualstudio.com/]VS
       Code(Free,Cross-platform,Plugins): same technology as atom but
       faster than atom, and Microsoft made.
     * [https://www.sublimetext.com/]Sublime Text(Free
       Evaluation,Cross-platform,Plugins): cross-platform, fast, and with
       plugins. Not free but can be freely used forever.
     * [https://www.jetbrains.com/]JetBrains(Free for Students,
       Cross-platform,Plugins): beautiful IDE's with many debugging and
       editing modes integrated.
     * [https://github.com/vim/vim]vim(Free,Cross-platform,Plugins): no
       words can describe the almighty vim.
          + [https://github.com/VundleVim/Vundle.vim]Vundle: the vim
            plugin manager
          + [https://github.com/amix/vimrc]vimrc from amix: "The ultimate
            Vim configuration: vimrc"

Softwares

     * [http://www.wolfram.com/mathematica/]Mathematica: One Software to
       Rule Them All
     * [http://ipython.org/notebook.html]iPython Notebook (Python): a
       useful tool for inline calculation, making graphs and writing
       notes.
          + [https://wakari.io/]wakari.io is a comercial one mostly aimed
            for data analysis.
          + [https://github.com/ptone/jiffylab]jiffylab is an open source
            one but not that well done.
          + [https://github.com/writefaruq/supervised-ipython-nbserver]sup
            ervised-ipython-nbserver is a multiuser version of notebook
            using Django/Pinax.
     * [http://www.mathworks.com/products/matlab/]Matlab
     * [https://www.rstudio.com/]RStudio (R)

Scientific Computing

     * [https://www.python.org/]Python
          + [https://www.scipy.org/]scipy: scientific computing made easy
          + [https://jiffyclub.github.io/snakeviz/]SnakeViz: A nice tool
            for python debugging and performance improvement.
