Academic

Self-plagiarism

   This might be not so straightforward but remember this. Reuse your own
   work doesn't protect you from plagiarism! Read it on
     * [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plagiarism#Self-plagiarism]wikipedia
       :Plagiarism#Self-plagiarism.

Investigate Papers

     * [https://meta.science/]Meta: Find the latest papers related to your
       own projects.
     * [http://paperscape.org/]Paperscape: Finding interesting papers.
     * [https://peer.us/]Peerus: Monitor specific topics or journal for
       new and relevant papers.
     * [https://scirate.com/]SciRate: An front-end for arXiv with rates
       from readers.

Get Yourself A Citable Code for Anything

     * [https://zenodo.org/]Zenodo: Make anything from GitHub citable by
       getting a DOI code here.

Add Citations to Your Code

     * [https://github.com/duecredit/duecredit]duecredit: Allows you to
       add decorators to Python functions that encode bibliographic
       details.

Open Science

     * [https://osf.io/]Open Science Framework: A open science tool with a
       lot of integrations.

Bibliography

     * [https://www.jabref.org/]JabRef: An open source bibliography
       reference manager for the BibTeX format.
     * [https://www.mendeley.com/]Mendeley: A bibliography reference
       manager with cloud storage and BibTeX support.
     * [https://www.zotero.org/]Zotero: An open source bibliography
       reference manager with syncing and BibTeX support.

Tips for Researchers

     * [http://collections.plos.org/ten-simple-rules]Ten Simple Rules by
       PLoS One: Series of quick "Ten Simple Rules" articles for research
       scientists to manage challenges in their careers. Number of
       articles are life-science specific, but rest the of articles are
       general enough for any researcher.
     * Check the
       [https://github.com/jivoi/awesome-osint#-academic-resources-and-gre
       y-literature]Academic Resources and Grey Literature List of the
       [https://github.com/jivoi/awesome-osint]Awesome Open-Source
       Intelligence List for search engines to search for papers.

Pacifier

   [http://www.rainymood.com/]Rainy Mood,
   [https://coffitivity.com/]Coffitivity and
   [http://www.noisli.com/]Noisli are the recommended ones.
     * [http://www.rainymood.com/]Rainy Mood(iOS, Android, Web): rainy day
       rainy mood, simple but with excellent white noise; a new beautiful
       soundtrack each day
     * [http://coffitivity.com/]Coffitivity(iOS, Android, Web, Mac): a
       rather simple but useful coffee shop noise library; premium has
       more three more soundtracks; elegant UI; scientific research
       powered
     * [https://www.brain.fm/]Brain.fm(Web): Improve Focus, Relaxation &
       Sleep with audio brainwave training. Not free but worth every
       penny.
     * [http://noiz.io/]Noizio(iOS, Mac): a handy white noise tool that
       stays in your Mac status bar.
     * [http://www.noisli.com/]Noisli (iOS, Android, Web, Chrome): free
       mixing of multiple tracks (which is similar to Soundrown but with
       much better UI). Users can save a customized setting for later use.
       I personally think this one has better fire sound tracks than
       soundrown.
     * [http://soundrown.com/]Soundrown(Web): free mixing of multiple
       tracks
     * [http://sleep.muji.net/]Muji Sleep(iOS, Android)
     * [http://asoftmurmur.com/]A Soft Murmur(Web): free mixing of
       multiple tracks; simple UI; Timer provided; Meander available
     * [https://mynoise.net/noiseMachines.php]mynoise(iOS, Web): a noise
       generator; a lot of choices (too many actually); detailed equalizer
     * [http://rainycafe.com/]Rainy Cafe(Web): not much to say just a
       combination of rainy mood and coffitivity
     * [http://www.clearskyapps.com/portfolio/sleep]Sleep Pillow(iOS,
       Mac): click and play style preloaded scenes; easy to use; beautiful
       design
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KZV9FmHOsRg]A youtube audio track
       of coffee shop (really long)
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s_2FDRtFOAw]A youtube audio track
       of 10 hours rain fall
     * [https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=air.com.demute.TaoMi
       x]TaoMix (Android): sound mixings to concentrate
     * [http://www.calm.com/]Calm(iOS, Android, Web): to help you calming
       down
     * [http://raining.fm/]Raining(iOS, Android, Web): raining and thunder
     * [https://www.focusatwill.com/]focus@will(iOS, Android, Web): music
       to boost your brain; paid services now

   Some Other Related Stuff
     * [http://www.iserenity.com/]iSerenity: multiple choices but not that
       good (just my feeling).
     * [https://rain.simplynoise.com/]Rany by simply noise: just rain.
     * [http://www.naturesoundplayer.com/]Natural Sound player: many
       natural sounds, cool.
     * [http://naturesoundsfor.me/]NatureSoundsFor.Me: make your own
       track, so many kinds of sounds.
     * [http://whitenoise247.net/]White.Noise: several different tracks
     * [http://www.ambient-mixer.com/]ambient mixer: make ambient sound
       easily
     * [http://whitenoisemp3s.com/]white noise mp3s: listen and download

